SIMPLE: hinder
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hinder
<hw>Hind"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>hindere</ets>, AS. hinder, adv., behind; akin to OHG.
<ets>hintar</ets>, prep., behind, G. <ets>hinter</ets>, Goth.
<ets>hindar</ets>; orig. a comparative, and akin to AS. <ets>hine</ets>
hence. See <er>Hence</er>, <er>He</er>, and cf. <er>Hind</er>,
<pos>a.</pos>, <er>Hindmost</er>.]</ety> <def>Of or belonging to that
part or end which is in the rear, or which follows; <as>as, the
<ex>hinder</ex> part of a wagon; the <ex>hinder</ex> parts of a
horse.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He was in the <qex>hinder</qex> part of the ship.</q>
<rj><qau>Mark iv. 38.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hinder</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Hinder
<hw>Hin"der</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Hindered</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Hindering</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE.
<ets>hindren</ets>, <ets>hinderen</ets>, AS. <ets>hindrian</ets>, fr.
<ets>hinder</ets> behind; akin to D. <ets>hinderen</ets>, G.
<ets>hindern</ets>, OHG. <ets>hintar<?/n</ets>, Icel. & Sw.
<ets>hindra</ets>, Dan. <ets>hindre</ets>. See <er>Hinder</er>,
<pos>a.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To keep back or behind; to prevent
from starting or moving forward; to check; to retard; to obstruct; to
bring to a full stop; -- often followed by <xex>from</xex>; <as>as, an
accident <ex>hindered</ex> the coach; drought <ex>hinders</ex> the
growth of plants; to <ex>hinder</ex> me from going.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Them that were entering in ye <qex>hindered</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Luke xi. 52.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I <qex>hinder</qex> you too long.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To prevent or embarrass; to debar; to shut
out.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>What <qex>hinders</qex> younger brothers, being fathers of
families, from having the same right?</q> <rj><qau>Locke.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To check; retard; impede; delay; block; clog;
prevent; stop; interrupt; counteract; thwart; oppose; obstruct; debar;
embarrass.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hinder</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Hinder
<hw>Hin"der</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To interpose obstacles or
impediments; to be a hindrance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>This objection <qex>hinders</qex> not but that the heroic action
of some commander . . . may be written.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hinderance</ent>⟦br⟧
